{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501606","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501606"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:30:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:30:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1770"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1770","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1770"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.08,0.44,0.07,0.22]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1770"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111306"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1770","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1770"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1770"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93440"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"527"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9112"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"9599"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12913"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"279"},{"type":"contributions","id":"16374"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34143"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35972"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42395"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44520"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45228"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111306","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/111306"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 46-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a two week history of right sided abdominal pain and three days of diarrhoea. She is otherwise well. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. On examination her pulse rate is 100/min, blood pressure 124/82mmHg, and temperature 37.6\u00b0C. Abdominal examination reveals a soft abdomen, apart from a tender 8 cm mass in the right iliac fossa. A CT scan is performed (Image 1, 2).\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate plan of management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Laparoscopic appendicectomy","Antibiotics and surveillance","Antibiotics and percutaneous drainage","Right hemicolectomy","Antibiotics and interval appendicectomy"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe CT scan shows a heterogeneous mass in the right iliac fossa containing locules of gas. This is almost certainly an appendix phlegmon, complicated by abscess formation. This is defined as complicated appendicitis with a large abscess.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn a case of uncomplicated appendicitis and in an otherwise well patient, \u003Cstrong\u003Eantibiotics and surveillance\u003C/strong\u003E would be considered an appropriate management option. An alternative option would have been appendicectomy. These options cannot be considered in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith this large abscess cavity, the patient will require \u003Cstrong\u003Eantibiotics and drainage.\u003C/strong\u003E It should be feasible to do this percutaneously under CT control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhere the appendicitis has been complicated by a small abscess formation, a reasonable plan of management would be \u003Cstrong\u003Eantibiotics following by interval appendicectomy.\u003C/strong\u003E Depending on the response to this conservative approach, more active intervention might be needed - such as percutaneous drainage or emergency appendicectomy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFor cases of complicated appendicitis with small abscess formation, there has been a recent shift to immediate appendicectomy. Several retrospective studies have shown that - performed in experienced hands - immediate appendicectomy is a safe option and associated with a reduced hospital stay compared with the conservative approach. A laparoscopic approach is preferred, as it allows a good inspection of the peritoneal cavity, with a more rapid postoperative recovery and reduced long term risk of adhesion formation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt must be noted that all the studies advocating prompt \u003Cstrong\u003Elaparoscopic appendicectomy\u003C/strong\u003E are retrospective in nature, were based on small sample sizes and the procedures undertaken by senior surgeons. Controlled trials will be needed to formalise this approach to the management of the appendix and whilst they are awaited, conservative measures cannot be criticised.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no current indication for \u003Cstrong\u003Eright hemicolectomy, \u003C/strong\u003Eas the underlying problem is almost certainly acute appendicitis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["In cases of complicated appendicitis with large abscess formation, percutaneous drainage is advocated."],"references":["Forsyth J, Lasithiotakis K, Peter M. The evolving management of the appendix mass in the era of laparoscopy and interventional radiology. Surgeon. 2017;15(2):109-115. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27612947/","Rajah KH, Menon S, Ramachandran G. Current management of appendicular mas - a narrative review. Med J Malaysia 2023; 78:669-74. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37775496/","Diaz JJ, Ceresoli M, Herron T, et al. Current management of acute appendicitis in adults: What you need to know. J Trauma Acute Care Surg. 2025; 98: 181\u2013189"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93440"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1770"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"22028"},{"type":"media","id":"22029"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"22028","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/22028"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/OmpNod6srWCoXcvbZN4AbiL8ps5WwQ.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/OmpNod6srWCoXcvbZN4AbiL8ps5WwQ.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":814,"height":616}},{"type":"media","id":"22029","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/22029"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/irqx51yyoWn0jbyVQK5arVdebTGS1Y.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/irqx51yyoWn0jbyVQK5arVdebTGS1Y.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":609,"height":736}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93440","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/93440"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-12T11:25:01+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-12T11:26:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1770"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111306"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt